# PLUMED 2.9 multi-walker WT-MetaD template for PfTrpS(Ain) TrpB benchmark
#
# ⚠️ DEPRECATED — DO NOT USE THIS TEMPLATE AS-IS (FP-022, 2026-04-08)
#
# This template predates two related bug fixes:
#   1. FP-020: PATHMSD does not work with non-sequential atom serials in
#      multi-model PDBs through the GROMACS mdrun + PLUMED interface.
#      We switched to FUNCPATHMSD (one RMSD action per frame).
#   2. FP-022: The LAMBDA value below (3.3910) was computed using the
#      "total SD" convention (sum of squared displacements over all 112
#      atoms). PLUMED's RMSD action emits per-atom-normalized values, so
#      the correct LAMBDA under the SQUARED convention is N_atoms = 112×
#      larger: 379.77 nm⁻². See FP-022 in failure-patterns.md.
#
# CORRECT TEMPLATE: see replication/metadynamics/single_walker/plumed.dat
# (uses FUNCPATHMSD + RMSD ... SQUARED + LAMBDA=379.77).
# OR run replication/metadynamics/path_cv/generate_path_cv.py — it now
# auto-emits a ready-to-use plumed_path_cv.dat snippet that you can include
# directly, eliminating manual copy-paste of LAMBDA.
#
# The 10-walker variant of the corrected setup needs WALKERS_N=10 +
# WALKERS_DIR=../ added to the METAD line. See the feature/10-walker-metad
# branch for the multi-walker scaffolding (which itself MUST be updated
# with the FP-022 fix before production use).
#
# This file is kept only for historical reference.
# ============================================================================

# Reference protocol: JACS 2019 SI
#   - CVs: path collective variables s(R), z(R)
#   - WT-MetaD: HEIGHT = 0.15 kcal/mol = 0.628 kJ/mol
#   - PACE = 1000 steps (2 ps at dt = 0.002 ps)
#   - BIASFACTOR = 10
#   - TEMP = 350 K
#   - Adaptive Gaussian widths
#
# FP-004 guard:
#   The PATHMSD reference PDB and all monitored atom indices must come from the
#   converted GROMACS topology/coordinate set, not from the input AMBER/PDB order.
#
# LAMBDA source (HISTORICAL — NOW WRONG, see FP-022):
#   replication/structures/path_frames/summary.txt
#   Mean total SD   = 67.826 A^2  ← total SD, NOT what PLUMED expects
#   lambda(total)   = 0.033910 A^-2  ← wrong by factor 112
#   GROMACS uses nm: lambda_nm2 = 0.033910 * 100 = 3.3910 nm^-2  (FP-018)
#   ★ CORRECT: lambda_nm2 = 2.3 / per-atom MSD = 2.3 / 0.006056 = 379.77 nm^-2
#
# SIGMA=0.05 is the initial seed for ADAPTIVE=GEOM.
# PLUMED automatically adjusts Gaussian widths based on local CV fluctuations.
# This matches the SI protocol (adaptive Gaussian widths).

# PATHMSD outputs two components:
#   path.sss -> progress along the O->C path
#   path.zzz -> distance from the reference path
#
# ⚠️ FP-020: PATHMSD does not handle non-sequential atom serials in multi-model
# PDB through GROMACS mdrun. Use FUNCPATHMSD with one RMSD action per frame.
# ⚠️ FP-022: LAMBDA=3.3910 is WRONG. Correct value is 379.77 (with SQUARED).
path: PATHMSD REFERENCE=PLACEHOLDER_PENDING_CONVERSION_PATH_REFERENCE_PDB LAMBDA=3.3910  # ⚠️ DEPRECATED, see header

# Monitoring-only distances; not biased.
k82_q2: DISTANCE ATOMS=PLACEHOLDER_PENDING_CONVERSION_K82_NZ_Q2_C
e104_q2: DISTANCE ATOMS=PLACEHOLDER_PENDING_CONVERSION_E104_OE_Q2_C

# Multi-walker WT-MetaD. submit_metad_walkers.sh substitutes __WALKER_ID__.
# FP-019: all METAD parameters on one line (no backslash continuation for GROMACS 2026 compatibility)
metad: METAD ARG=path.sss,path.zzz SIGMA=0.05 ADAPTIVE=GEOM HEIGHT=0.628 PACE=1000 BIASFACTOR=10 TEMP=350 FILE=../shared_bias/HILLS WALKERS_N=10 WALKERS_ID=__WALKER_ID__ WALKERS_DIR=../shared_bias WALKERS_RSTRIDE=1000

PRINT ARG=path.sss,path.zzz,k82_q2,e104_q2,metad.bias FILE=COLVAR STRIDE=500
